ABUJA – Governors and leaders from the Northern part of the country have dumped the idea of the President of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan, standing for the 2023 presidency on the platform of All Progressive Congress, The Eagleonline reports The position of the Governors and Leaders from the North was contained in a statement they issued on Saturday. The statement came as a meeting President Muhammadu Buhari summoned with Governors elected on the platform of the APC began at the Presidential Villa, Abuja. The Northern Governors and Leaders are pushing for a Southern presidential candidate for the party. They argued that after eight years of President Muhammadu Buhari’s presidency, it should be the turn of the South. According to information in the political space, the President had settled for Lawan in order to counter the Peoples Democratic Party, which will be fielding former Vice President Atiku Abubakar as presidential candidate for the 2023 elections. See their statement: Northern power brokers are back in the trenches, scheming how the region will retain political power in the country in 2023. Their plan is to ensure that as many presidential aspirants as possible emerge from the south while they would prop up a single aspirant from the region to slug… In "Opinion" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The President of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan on Saturday visited Jigawa to canvas support for his Presidential bid ahead of the upcoming primaries of the All Progressives Congress(APC). While at Dutse, the capital city of Jigawa State, Lawan and his campaign team paid… In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The President of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan said on Thursday that his presidential bid is in his capacity as a Nigerian who is qualified to be President and not as a northern aspirant as is being insinuated in some quarters."I am not running… In "Top Stories"